      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not a prank though. i've lived here for two years and they've never even looked at me, and now this? it's way too perfect. and the signal thing... it's not just \"being in range.\" it feels like the signal is actually FOLLOWING me. like as soon as I head toward the back of the house, the bars just max out. if it was just a normal signal, wouldn't it be strongest near the wall they share with me? why would it get stronger when i'm further away? it feels like they're using some kind of directional tech to pin down my exact location.",
